#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Eye-puzzle cryptanalysis harness.

A single self-contained script that reproduces every structural finding from
CRYPTANALYSIS.md, in order. Each section is a function that:

  - Computes a structured result from the corpus,
  - Prints a human-readable report,
  - Asserts the headline numbers we have publicly committed to.

Run all sections:

    python eye/cryptanalysis_harness.py

Run a single section:

    python eye/cryptanalysis_harness.py 11        # section 11 only
    python eye/cryptanalysis_harness.py 7..11     # sections 7-11

The harness is intentionally pure-Python (no NumPy / SciPy) so that every
computation is auditable. Only standard library is used. Sections **45–46**
(MPR / Noita PRNG enumeration) dominate wall time; sections **92, 93, 98**
(Monte-Carlo significance tests for the peer-review-reconciliation block)
and **102** (cumulative SAFE/UNSAFE distance sweep) each add ~5-25 s.
Sections **133–136** add substantial CPU separately (§133’s articulator
stream is tens of seconds; §136 uses a **spawn** ``multiprocessing.Pool``
θ scan unless ``EYE_SKIP_ARTIC_THETA_SCAN=1`` replays pinned goldens).
Sections **137–226** are fast (§137 duplex × shell-multiplicity coupling pins;
§138 §128-remainder injective bookkeeping vs naive ``∏ |D|`` patches; §139
alnum-36 / numbered-list plaintext hypothesis + CP-SAT alphabet hook; §140
primered CT-autokey lane diagnostics; §141 deterministic XGAK transition probe;
§142 complete-component injective remainder bound; §143 noncomplete 29-patch
clique packing, ~10 s; §144 optional alnum-36 CP-SAT assertion; §145 exact
29-patch articulation count; §146 exact complete-component counts; §147 optional
K=25 colour-structure probe; §§148–151 residual/template/XGAK probes;
§§152–156 W1[101] arc; §§157–166 structural recalibration revealing
the W2[92] hyper-junction; §§167–178 W2[92] arc; §§179–186 BK clique
enumeration (K₂₆/K₂₄), bridge cell census; §§187–198 K₂₆/K₂₄ apex
probes, bridge×mega18 disjointness check, all-cliques structural
profile, multi-articulation joint deletion, non-giant cliques (every
non-giant component is a complete graph), MIS lower bound + χ ≥ 26,
per-label clique participation (≈ 99%), K₂₆/K₂₄ edge completeness,
1-edge perturbation collapse (K₂₆ → 2×K₂₅), triangle distribution,
giant diameter = 8 with center E3[50]).
§§199–209 falsify the role-guided over-merge, pivot to
PLAINTEXT_SKELETON, recover the skeleton-level 91-block σ table, print
family-aligned grids, test the universal ``". "`` header pin, and
red-team that crib against off-header contexts / universal-pair nulls,
atomic-digraph nulls, phrase segmentation, 91-block incidence, crib-ledger
constraints, post-atom body alignment, punctuation-atom search, and
word-space candidate search.
§§220–222 export crib-pinned skeleton artifacts and hard scoring hooks
for downstream language-model/text-identification runs. §§223–225 scan
local repo/game text assets, audit existing SA pin usage, and provide a
minimal hard-constraint scorer. §226 audits the fresh skeleton-native
crib-pinned SA runner.
§§227–232 GAK/deck structural probes (adjacent-different-σ, 2D key census,
reading-order sweep, XGAK near-identity σ, Lymm cross-row isomorph %,
PT-feedback table vs §141 CT-feedback); §233 consolidated GAK verdict;
§234 construction-output audit; §235 PT-feedback skeleton vs UF keys;
§236 dist-4 synthesis screen; §237 strict vs relaxed XGAK tables; §238 construction plaintext-pattern audit; §239 v4 template repair;
§240 artifact regression gate (v5 promoted, forbidden shards);
§241 allomorph null-model lexical smoke gate; §242 dist-4-targeted synthesis screen;
§244 §222 pin/class/injectivity regression gate on pinned constructions;
§246 v5 prose-heuristic vs per-message shuffle null.
``make -C eye gak-construction-smoke`` runs §227–249 (present sections only).
``python3 eye/ingest_construction_candidate.py`` for LLM/solver candidate JSON.
Sections **103-107** (constructive cipher
synthesis) add ~3 s combined. End-to-end wall time scales with how many sections
you select; legacy “few minutes total” summaries predate Tarjan-megagraph blocks.

Sections **91–98** (the *peer-review reconciliation* block) reconcile our
findings against external audits — currently 2quacks 2026-05-11 — and
formalize the rebuttals to claims we accept-but-reinterpret. See §91 for
the index.

Sections **99–102** (additional structural constraints) tighten the
constraint surface for any candidate cipher: σ-rotation positional
invariants, σ-key entry-count distribution (no saturation), the
universal-prelude σ_0 cross-msg pin theorem, and the safe/unsafe same-ct
merge distance separation theorem.

Sections **103–107** invert the analysis pipeline.  Where §1-§102 reverse-
engineer structural facts from the real ciphertext, §103-§107 *forward-
generate* synthetic corpora from a parameterized cipher specification (in
`eye/cipher_synthesis.py`) and screen them through the §96 validator and
the §99-§102 invariants.  Whatever cipher families pass everything are
*candidate hypotheses* about the actual cipher — see §107's family sweep
for the constraint-surface map.

If any assertion fails, the harness exits non-zero with a clear marker. If
any number deviates from CRYPTANALYSIS.md, that's a bug in either the script
or the writeup.
"""

